&lt;section data-test-id=&quot;activity-full-description&quot; data-v-1ab49a27=&quot;&quot; data-v-4f4223ef=&quot;&quot;&gt;Full description
&lt;section data-v-4f4223ef=&quot;&quot; data-v-fda1f212=&quot;&quot;&gt;If your time in Milan is limited, or if you want an overview to guide your exploration, this one-day walking tour is the perfect introduction, taking in all the most prominent sights &amp;mdash; including guaranteed entry to see Da Vinci&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;The Last Supper&amp;rsquo;. Led by your local, English-speaking guide, you&amp;rsquo;ll visit some iconic sights and some off the beaten track. You&amp;rsquo;ll get to skip the line at Milan Duomo and experience this world-famous cathedral without waiting &amp;mdash; unlike the city itself, which waited nearly 600 years for the incredible building to be completed. The tour will pause again so you can admire the medieval Sforza Castle (from the outside only), before delving into the cobbled streets of the Brera district. This is the beating heart of Milan&amp;rsquo;s social and cultural life, as your guide will explain. You&amp;rsquo;ll hear about all the famous artists and thinkers that have called Brera home, as well as some more up-to-date recommendations of places to revisit later for a drink or a meal. The climactic part of the tour is a viewing of Leonardo Da Vinci&amp;rsquo;s phenomenal mural, &amp;lsquo;The Last Supper&amp;rsquo;. Often imitated, never bettered, this masterpiece is carefully preserved, and only one group is allowed to view it at a time. This can make tickets a challenge to acquire, but yours are included in this package, along with special Skip-the-Line access &amp;mdash; so you&amp;rsquo;re guaranteed your full 15 minutes with the fresco. Listen as your guide points out the details that earn &amp;lsquo;The Last Supper&amp;rsquo; its place in the history books. After just one day, you&amp;rsquo;ll find your relationship to Milan forever changed for the better.&lt;br /&gt;
